      "actionDate": "2026-04-20",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in House",
      "text": "<p>This bill authorizes the Capitol Police Board to waive the mandatory retirement age for members of the Capitol Police up to age 65. (Under current law, a member of the Capitol Police is generally subject to mandatory retirement&nbsp;at age 57 but may receive a waiver from the board authorizing later retirement up to age 60.)&nbsp;</p>",
      "updateDate": "2026-04-24T17:54:21Z",
